article.headline: Utah Valley State 74, IPFW 57
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- David Heck scored 17 points and was one of five Utah Valley State players to score in double figures in a 74-57 victory Saturday over Indiana-Purdue-Fort Wayne. The win is the fifth in a row for the Wolverines (9-9), who improved to .500 for the first time this season. After winning their first game under interim head coach Joe Pechota, the Mastodons (4-15) have now lost two straight. David Simon led IPFW with 17 points and Quintin Butler added 11 points. Ronnie Price scored 16, Pierre Thomas had 13 points, Josh Cottle scored 11 and Ben Devoe added 10 points for Utah Valley State. IPFW cut Utah Valley's 13-point lead down to five with 5:34 left in the game, but the Wolverines scored 10 straight points to put away the Mastodons. Price had been averaging 31.1 points at home, but is playing with an injured wrist and tailbone.
